      "message": "This doesn’t actually work in NDK r14 for 32-bit MIPS with clang. Every compiler invocation spews this:\n\nclang38++: error: argument unused during compilation: \u0027-L/Users/mark/android-ndk-r14_mips_api16/bin/../lib/gcc/mips64el-linux-android/4.9.x/32/mips-r1/\u0027\n\nIt’s a warning which, due to our use of -Werror, becomes an error.\n\nThat’s coming from https://android.googlesource.com/platform/ndk/+/ndk-r14/build/tools/make_standalone_toolchain.py#234.\n\nThe problem has been fixed in the NDK master (https://android.googlesource.com/platform/ndk/+/40d8abbf40e0556ccfa5598ff8c4ac8c1e141934) and we don’t currently support MIPS anyway, so I’m just going to leave this as-is, quietly undocumented, and hope that it starts working when there’s a new NDK release.",
